## **1.8 Essential Grammatical Elements in ggplot2: stat**

### **1.8.1 Working with `stat()`**


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(y = MATHS, x= GENDER)) +
  geom_boxplot()
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](Hands-on_Exercise1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-20-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


### **1.8.2 Working with stat - the *stat_summary()* method**

### [`stat_summary()`](https://ggplot2.tidyverse.org/reference/stat_summary.html) function


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(y = MATHS, x= GENDER)) +
  geom_boxplot()
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](Hands-on_Exercise1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-21-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


### **1.8.2 Working with stat - the *stat_summary()* method** [`stat_summary()`](https://ggplot2.tidyverse.org/reference/stat_summary.html) 


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(y = MATHS, x= GENDER)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  stat_summary(geom = "point",       
               fun = "mean",         
               colour ="red",        
               linewidth=4)               
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](Hands-on_Exercise1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-22-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


### **1.8.3 Working with stat - the `geom()` method**


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(y = MATHS, x= GENDER)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  geom_point(stat="summary",        
             fun="mean",           
             colour="red",          
             linewidth=4)          
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](Hands-on_Exercise1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-23-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


### **1.8.4 Adding a best fit curve on a scatterplot?**

[`geom_smooth()`](https://ggplot2.tidyverse.org/reference/geom_smooth.html) 


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(x= MATHS, y=ENGLISH)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(linewidth=0.5)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](Hands-on_Exercise1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-24-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::



::: {.cell}

:::



::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(x= MATHS, 
           y=ENGLISH)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method=lm, 
              linewidth=0.5)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](Hands-on_Exercise1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-26-1.png){width=672}
