## **1.9 Essential Grammatical Elements in ggplot2: Facets**

[`facet_grid()`](https://ggplot2.tidyverse.org/reference/facet_grid.html) and [`facet_wrap`](https://ggplot2.tidyverse.org/reference/facet_wrap.html)

### **1.9.1 Working with `facet_wrap()`**


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(x= MATHS)) +
  geom_histogram(bins=20) +
    facet_wrap(~ CLASS)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](Hands-on_Exercise1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-27-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


### **1.9.2 `facet_grid()` function**


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(x= MATHS)) +
  geom_histogram(bins=20) +
    facet_grid(~ CLASS)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](Hands-on_Exercise1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-28-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


## **1.10 Essential Grammatical Elements in ggplot2: Coordinates**

\- \[\`coord_cartesian()\`\](https://ggplot2.tidyverse.org/reference/coord_cartesian.html): the default cartesian coordinate systems, where you specify x and y values (e.g. allows you to zoom in or out). - \[\`coord_flip()\`\](https://ggplot2.tidyverse.org/reference/coord_flip.html): a cartesian system with the x and y flipped. - \[\`coord_fixed()\`\](https://ggplot2.tidyverse.org/reference/coord_fixed.html): a cartesian system with a "fixed" aspect ratio (e.g. 1.78 for a "widescreen" plot). - \[\`coord_quickmap()\`\](https://ggplot2.tidyverse.org/reference/coord_map.html): a coordinate system that approximates a good aspect ratio for maps.

\
**1.10.1 Working with Coordinate**


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(x=RACE)) +
  geom_bar()
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](Hands-on_Exercise1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-29-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::



::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(x=RACE)) +
  geom_bar() +
  coord_flip()
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](Hands-on_Exercise1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-30-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


### **1.10.2 Changing the y- and x-axis range**


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(x= MATHS, y=ENGLISH)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method=lm, linewidth=0.5)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](Hands-on_Exercise1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-31-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::



::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(x= MATHS, y=ENGLISH)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method=lm, 
              linewidth=0.5) +  
  coord_cartesian(xlim=c(0,100),
                  ylim=c(0,100))
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](Hands-on_Exercise1_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-32-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


